retirementReasons: Duplicate of entry MITE0000035, which was retained because of a more extensive reaction list. All data has been transferred to MITE0000035.
comment: Acyltransferase can use acyl-CoA of different acyl chain length and glucosamine free as UDP-glucosamine or bound to hpg4 of teicoplanin pseudoaglycone as substrates.

changelog.comment: Initial entry. Reviewer 1 fixed reaction SMARTS but had to remove the balanced substrate/product SMILES due to issues with phosphorous chemistry in RDKit. Reviewer 1 retired entry in favor of MITE0000035.

reactions.description: Deacetylates N-acetylglucosaminyl residue on Hpg4 of the teicoplanin precursor.
Reaction does not occure naturally during teicoplanin biosynthesis; acyl-CoA as co-substrate.
